uestionRevisions","id":"81525","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/81525"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EThe Australian Government\u0027s Closing the Gap framework represents a commitment to improve health outcomes for Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples. The framework was revised in 2020 through a historic partnership between Australian governments and Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peak organisations.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes a key principle of the Closing the Gap framework?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Shared decision-making with Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples","Focusing exclusively on medical interventions","Implementing standardised approaches across all communities","Centralising all healthcare services in major cities","Prioritising acute care over preventative health measures"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe correct answer is \u003Cstrong\u003Eshared decision-making with Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples\u003C/strong\u003E. This principle recognises that Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples must be genuine partners in developing and implementing strategies to improve health outcomes. This approach ensures culturally appropriate solutions and community ownership of health initiatives.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EFocusing exclusively on medical interventions\u003C/strong\u003E - The framework recognises that health outcomes are influenced by multiple factors including social, cultural, and economic determinants, not just medical care\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ECentralising all healthcare services in major cities\u003C/strong\u003E - This would reduce accessibility for many Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, particularly those in remote communities\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImplementing standardised approaches across all communities\u003C/strong\u003E - This fails to recognise the diversity of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander communities and their specific needs\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPrioritising acute care over preventative health measures\u003C/strong\u003E - The framework emphasises the importance of preventative health and early intervention alongside acute care\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe success of Closing the Gap initiatives depends on genuine partnership, cultural safety, and community-led solutions that address both immediate health needs and broader social determinants of health.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The Closing the Gap framework aims to achieve health equity between Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples and non-Indigenous Australians by 2031.","Key targets include increasing life expectancy, reducing infant mortality, and improving access to culturally safe healthcare services.","Social determinants of health significantly impact health outcomes for Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples."],"references":["https://www.closingthegap.gov.au/"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"66869"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"19162"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"66869","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/66869"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-01-26T07:42:01+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-02-14T20:33:56+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11896"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"81525"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"17","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/17"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude07","name":"Bioethics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"created